msgstr "but why did he say it? "

msgctxt "mn114:7.6"
msgid "Yathārūpaṃ, bhante, manosamācāraṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti evarūpo manosamācāro na sevitabbo; "
msgstr "You should not cultivate the kind of mental behavior which causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

msgctxt "mn114:7.7"
msgid "yathārūpañca kho, bhante, manosamācāraṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti evarūpo manosamācāro sevitabbo. "
msgstr "And you should cultivate the kind of mental behavior which causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.50, sc11
msgctxt "mn114:7.8"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, manosamācāraṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti? "
msgstr "And what kind of mental behavior causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline? "

msgctxt "mn114:7.9"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ abhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti; "
msgstr "It’s when someone is covetous. They covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’ "

msgctxt "mn114:7.10"
msgid "byāpannacitto kho pana hoti paduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā haññantu vā vajjhantu vā ucchijjantu vā vinassantu vā mā vā ahesun’ti—"
msgstr "They have ill will and hateful intentions: ‘May these sentient beings be killed, slaughtered, slain, destroyed, or annihilated!’ "

msgctxt "mn114:7.11"
msgid "evarūpaṃ, bhante, manosamācāraṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti. "
msgstr "That kind of mental behavior causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn114:7.12"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, manosamācāraṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti? "
msgstr "And what kind of mental behavior causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow? "

msgctxt "mn114:7.13"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti, yaṃ taṃ parassa paravittūpakaraṇaṃ taṃ nābhijjhātā hoti: ‘aho vata yaṃ parassa taṃ mamassā’ti; "
msgstr "It’s when someone is content. They don’t covet the wealth and belongings of others: ‘Oh, if only their belongings were mine!’ "

#. VAR: abyābajjhā → abyāpajjhā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn114:7.14"
msgid "abyāpannacitto kho pana hoti appaduṭṭhamanasaṅkappo: ‘ime sattā averā abyābajjhā anīghā sukhī attānaṃ pariharantū’ti—"
msgstr "They have a kind heart and loving intentions: ‘May these sentient beings live free of enmity and ill will, untroubled and happy!’ "

msgctxt "mn114:7.15"
msgid "evarūpaṃ, bhante, manosamācāraṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti. "
msgstr "That kind of mental behavior causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

msgctxt "mn114:7.16"
msgid "‘Manosamācārampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two kinds of mental behavior: "

msgctxt "mn114:7.17"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:7.18"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ manosamācāran’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a kind of mental behavior.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:7.19"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, and this is why he said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, sc13
msgctxt "mn114:8.1"
msgid "‘Cittuppādampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two ways of giving rise to a thought: "

msgctxt "mn114:8.2"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.3"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ cittuppādan’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a way of giving rise to a thought.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:8.4"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, "

msgctxt "mn114:8.5"
msgid "Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "but why did he say it? "

msgctxt "mn114:8.6"
msgid "Yathārūpaṃ, bhante, cittuppādaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti evarūpo cittuppādo na sevitabbo; "
msgstr "You should not cultivate the way of giving rise to a thought which causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.7"
msgid "yathārūpañca kho, bhante, cittuppādaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti evarūpo cittuppādo sevitabbo. "
msgstr "And you should cultivate the way of giving rise to a thought which causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn114:8.8"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, cittuppādaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti? "
msgstr "And what way of giving rise to a thought causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline? "

msgctxt "mn114:8.9"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti, abhijjhāsahagatena cetasā viharati; "
msgstr "It’s when someone is covetous, and lives with their heart full of covetousness. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.10"
msgid "byāpādavā hoti, byāpādasahagatena cetasā viharati; "
msgstr "They are malicious, and live with their heart full of ill will. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.11"
msgid "vihesavā hoti, vihesāsahagatena cetasā viharati—"
msgstr "They’re hurtful, and live with their heart intent on harm. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.12"
msgid "evarūpaṃ, bhante, cittuppādaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti. "
msgstr "That way of giving rise to a thought causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.51, sc15
msgctxt "mn114:8.13"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, cittuppādaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti? "
msgstr "And what way of giving rise to a thought causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow? "

msgctxt "mn114:8.14"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco anabhijjhālu hoti, anabhijjhāsahagatena cetasā viharati; "
msgstr "It’s when someone is content, and lives with their heart full of contentment. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.15"
msgid "abyāpādavā hoti, abyāpādasahagatena cetasā viharati; "
msgstr "They have good will, and live with their heart full of good will. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.16"
msgid "avihesavā hoti, avihesāsahagatena cetasā viharati—"
msgstr "They’re kind, and live with their heart full of kindness. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.17"
msgid "evarūpaṃ, bhante, cittuppādaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti. "
msgstr "That way of giving rise to a thought causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.18"
msgid "‘Cittuppādampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two ways of giving rise to a thought: "

msgctxt "mn114:8.19"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:8.20"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ cittuppādan’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a way of giving rise to a thought.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:8.21"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, and this is why he said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, sc16
msgctxt "mn114:9.1"
msgid "‘Saññāpaṭilābhampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two ways of acquiring perception: "

msgctxt "mn114:9.2"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:9.3"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ saññāpaṭilābhan’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a way of acquiring perception.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:9.4"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, "

msgctxt "mn114:9.5"
msgid "Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "but why did he say it? "

msgctxt "mn114:9.6"
msgid "Yathārūpaṃ, bhante, saññāpaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti evarūpo saññāpaṭilābho na sevitabbo; "
msgstr "You should not cultivate the way of acquiring perception which causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

msgctxt "mn114:9.7"
msgid "yathārūpañca kho, bhante, saññāpaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti evarūpo saññāpaṭilābho sevitabbo. "
msgstr "And you should cultivate the way of acquiring perception which causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "mn114:9.8"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, saññāpaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti? "
msgstr "And what way of acquiring perception causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline? "

msgctxt "mn114:9.9"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco abhijjhālu hoti, abhijjhāsahagatāya saññāya viharati; "
msgstr "It’s when someone is covetous, and lives with their perception full of covetousness. "

msgctxt "mn114:9.10"
msgid "byāpādavā hoti, byāpādasahagatāya saññāya viharati; "
msgstr "They are malicious, and live with their perception full of ill will. "

msgctxt "mn114:9.11"
msgid "vihesavā hoti, vihesāsahagatāya saññāya viharati—"
msgstr "They’re hurtful, and live with their perception intent on harm. "

msgctxt "mn114:9.12"
msgid "evarūpaṃ, bhante, saññāpaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti. "
msgstr "That way of acquiring perception causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "mn114:9.13"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, saññāpaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti? "
