msgctxt "mn114:9.17"
msgid "evarūpaṃ, bhante, saññāpaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti. "
msgstr "That way of acquiring perception causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

msgctxt "mn114:9.18"
msgid "‘Saññāpaṭilābhampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two ways of acquiring perception: "

msgctxt "mn114:9.19"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:9.20"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ saññāpaṭilābhan’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a way of acquiring perception.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:9.21"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, and this is why he said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, pts-vp-pli3.52, sc19
msgctxt "mn114:10.1"
msgid "‘Diṭṭhipaṭilābhampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two ways of acquiring views: "

msgctxt "mn114:10.2"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:10.3"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ diṭṭhipaṭilābhan’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a way of acquiring views.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:10.4"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, "

msgctxt "mn114:10.5"
msgid "Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "but why did he say it? "

msgctxt "mn114:10.6"
msgid "Yathārūpaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhipaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti evarūpo diṭṭhipaṭilābho na sevitabbo; "
msgstr "You should not cultivate the way of acquiring views which causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

msgctxt "mn114:10.7"
msgid "yathārūpañca kho, bhante, diṭṭhipaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti—evarūpo diṭṭhipaṭilābho sevitabbo. "
msgstr "And you should cultivate the way of acquiring views which causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "mn114:10.8"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhipaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti? "
msgstr "And what way of acquiring views causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline? "

msgctxt "mn114:10.9"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco evaṃdiṭṭhiko hoti: "
msgstr "It’s when someone has such a view: "

msgctxt "mn114:10.10"
msgid "‘natthi dinnaṃ, natthi yiṭṭhaṃ, natthi hutaṃ, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, natthi ayaṃ loko, natthi paro loko, natthi mātā, natthi pitā, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti—"
msgstr "‘There’s no meaning in giving, sacrifice, or offerings. There’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds. There’s no afterlife. There are no duties to mother and father. No beings are reborn spontaneously. And there’s no ascetic or brahmin who is well attained and practiced, and who describes the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:10.11"
msgid "evarūpaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhipaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti. "
msgstr "That way of acquiring views causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "mn114:10.12"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhipaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti? "
msgstr "And what way of acquiring views causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow? "

msgctxt "mn114:10.13"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco evaṃdiṭṭhiko hoti: "
msgstr "It’s when someone has such a view: "

msgctxt "mn114:10.14"
msgid "‘atthi dinnaṃ, atthi yiṭṭhaṃ, atthi hutaṃ, atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko, atthi ayaṃ loko, atthi paro loko, atthi mātā, atthi pitā, atthi sattā opapātikā, atthi loke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sammaggatā sammāpaṭipannā ye imañca lokaṃ parañca lokaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedentī’ti—"
msgstr "‘There is meaning in giving, sacrifice, and offerings. There are fruits and results of good and bad deeds. There is an afterlife. There are duties to mother and father. There are beings reborn spontaneously. And there are ascetics and brahmins who are well attained and practiced, and who describe the afterlife after realizing it with their own insight.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:10.15"
msgid "evarūpaṃ, bhante, diṭṭhipaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti. "
msgstr "That way of acquiring views causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

msgctxt "mn114:10.16"
msgid "‘Diṭṭhipaṭilābhampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two ways of acquiring views: "

msgctxt "mn114:10.17"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:10.18"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ diṭṭhipaṭilābhan’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a way of acquiring views.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:10.19"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, and this is why he said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, pts-vp-pli3.53, sc22
msgctxt "mn114:11.1"
msgid "‘Attabhāvapaṭilābhampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two ways of reincarnating: "

msgctxt "mn114:11.2"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:11.3"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhan’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a way of reincarnating.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:11.4"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, "

msgctxt "mn114:11.5"
msgid "Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "but why did he say it? "

msgctxt "mn114:11.6"
msgid "Yathārūpaṃ, bhante, attabhāvapaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti—"
msgstr "The way of reincarnating that causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline: "

msgctxt "mn114:11.7"
msgid "evarūpo attabhāvapaṭilābho na sevitabbo; "
msgstr "you should not cultivate that way of reincarnating. "

msgctxt "mn114:11.8"
msgid "yathārūpañca kho, bhante, attabhāvapaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti—"
msgstr "The way of reincarnating that causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow: "

msgctxt "mn114:11.9"
msgid "evarūpo attabhāvapaṭilābho sevitabbo. "
msgstr "you should cultivate that way of reincarnating. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc23
msgctxt "mn114:11.10"
msgid "Kathaṃrūpaṃ, bhante, attabhāvapaṭilābhaṃ sevato akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti? "
msgstr "And what way of reincarnating causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline? "

# NOTE: apariniṭṭhitabhāva is found only here, see BB’s note. At Thig 13.2 parinitthita means “prepared” food, and I follow that for lack of anything else.
#. VAR: Sabyābajjhaṃ → sabyāpajjhaṃ (bj, s2, s3, km, mr) | byāpajjhaṃ (s1) | savyāpajjhaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "mn114:11.11"
msgid "Sabyābajjhaṃ, bhante, attabhāvapaṭilābhaṃ abhinibbattayato apariniṭṭhitabhāvāya akusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti, kusalā dhammā parihāyanti; "
msgstr "Generating rebirth in a hurtful reincarnation, which because of its unpreparedness causes unskillful qualities to grow while skillful qualities decline. "

# NOTE: The question is present in the PTS edition, and its omission is presumably an oversight.
msgctxt "mn114:11.12"
msgid "abyābajjhaṃ, bhante, attabhāvapaṭilābhaṃ abhinibbattayato pariniṭṭhitabhāvāya akusalā dhammā parihāyanti, kusalā dhammā abhivaḍḍhanti. "
msgstr "And what way of reincarnating causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow? Generating rebirth in a pleasing reincarnation, which because of its preparedness causes unskillful qualities to decline while skillful qualities grow. "

msgctxt "mn114:11.13"
msgid "‘Attabhāvapaṭilābhampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "‘I say that there are two ways of reincarnating: "

msgctxt "mn114:11.14"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr "that which you should cultivate, and that which you should not cultivate. "

msgctxt "mn114:11.15"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ attabhāvapaṭilābhan’ti—"
msgstr "And each of these is a way of reincarnating.’ "

msgctxt "mn114:11.16"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what the Buddha said, and this is why he said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc24
msgctxt "mn114:12.1"
msgid "Imassa kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa, evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Sir, that’s how I understand the detailed meaning of the Buddha’s brief statement.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc25
msgctxt "mn114:13.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Sāriputta! "

msgctxt "mn114:13.2"
msgid "Sādhu kho tvaṃ, sāriputta, imassa mayā saṅkhittena bhāsitassa, vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa, evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāsi. "
msgstr "It’s good that you understand the detailed meaning of my brief statement in this way.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya14, sc26
msgctxt "mn114:14.1"
msgid "‘Kāyasamācārampāhaṃ, bhikkhave, duvidhena vadāmi—"
msgstr "And the Buddha went on to repeat and endorse Venerable Sāriputta’s explanation in full. Then he went on to explain further: "

msgctxt "mn114:14.2"
msgid "sevitabbampi, asevitabbampi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn114:14.3"
msgid "tañca aññamaññaṃ kāyasamācāran’ti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn114:14.4"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ mayā. "
